Abstract

Integrate after process samples individual. At this point, samples had already been filtered and regressed out for cell cycle, nFeature, nCount. But we only need the raw matrix after the cut-off.

PART 1: Integration

for (i in 1:3) {
  object.list[[i]] <- NormalizeData(object.list[[i]], verbose = FALSE)
  object.list[[i]] <- FindVariableFeatures(object.list[[i]], verbose = FALSE)
}
anchors <- FindIntegrationAnchors(object.list, dims = 1:30)
mash <- IntegrateData(anchors, dims = 1:30)
DefaultAssay(mash)
mash <- SCTransform(mash, vars.to.regress = c("percent.mt", "nCount_RNA", "nFeature_RNA", "S.Score", "G2M.Score"), verbose = FALSE)
mash <- RunPCA(mash, npcs = 20, verbose = FALSE)
mash <- JackStraw(mash, dims=20)
mash <- ScoreJackStraw(mash, dims = 1:20)
##### Wrapper function to get npcs automatically ####
getP <- function(object) {
  # object: Seurat object after running scorejackstraw
  pval <- object@reductions$pca@jackstraw$overall.p.values
  pick <-  pval[,1][which(pval[,2] > 0.0001)]
  pick <- pick[1]-1
  return(pick)
}
nPCs <- getP(mash)
nPCs
# saveRDS(mash, "Integrate.RDS")
# Choose npc 18 based on JackStrawPlot
JackStrawPlot(mash, dims = 1:20)

# Get the MK idents from original objects 
lungMK.df <- lungMK@meta.data[, "SCT_snn_res.0.5", drop = FALSE]
row.names(lungMK.df) <- paste0(row.names(lungMK.df), "_1")
lungMK.df$MK <- ifelse(lungMK.df$SCT_snn_res.0.5 == 7, "Lung_MK", NA)

row.names(lungTotal.df) <- paste0(row.names(lungTotal.df), "_2")

# Lung MKs have more common with DC than with BM MKs

                     BM_MK   = BMMK.markers, 
                     DC  = DC.markers)
up   <- lapply(markers, function(x) row.names(x)[(x$avg_logFC > 0 & x$p_val_adj < 0.001)])

goi <- lapply(markers.list, function(x) row.names(x))
goi <- unique(unlist(goi))

Heatmaps on cluster average Subset to just BM, Lung MKs, and DC

mash$tissueMKDC <- mash$tissueMerge
mash$tissueMKDC <- ifelse(is.na(mash$tissueMKDC), "NotMKDC", mash$tissueMKDC)
mash$tissueMKDC <- gsub("BM_DC", "DC", mash$tissueMKDC)
mash$tissueMKDC <- gsub("Lung_DC", "DC", mash$tissueMKDC)

novo <- subset(mash, subset = tissueMKDC != "NotMKDC")
novo <- SetIdent(novo, value = "tissueMKDC")
clusterAve <- AverageExpression(novo, assays = "RNA", use.scale = FALSE)$RNA
clusterAve <- clusterAve[row.names(clusterAve) %in% goi, ]
clusterAve <- clusterAve[complete.cases(clusterAve),]
Markers <- vector()
# This is very specific to case. 
# Base on a scratch venn diagram we draw earlier, BMMK markers are 100 and by itself. There are 3 genes overlapped between lung MK and DC. 
for (i in goi) {
  if (i %in% intersect(row.names(markers.list[[1]]), row.names(markers.list[[3]]))) {
    assign <- "Common between DC and Lung MK" 
  } else if (i %in% row.names(markers.list[[1]])) {
    assign <- "Lung MK Specific"
  } else if (i %in% row.names(markers.list[[2]])) {
    assign <- "BM MK Specific"
  } else {
    assign <- "DC Specific"
  }
  Markers <- c(Markers, assign)
}

annot <- data.frame(row.names = goi, 
                    Markers = Markers)
my_pal2 <- viridis::viridis_pal(option = "B")(300)

pheatmap(clusterAve, annotation_row = annot, color = my_pal2, fontsize_row = 5.5, scale = "row")
